DP blames police boss of being partisan and misusing the independent institution.Ruto claims the police have been abetting the actions of those interested in dividing the country along tribal lines. Deputy President William Ruto has cautioned the police against being used to cause chaos ahead of 2022 General Election.  

The DP blamed Inspector General of Police Hillary Mutyambai of being partisan and misusing the independent institution by taking orders from other quarters.  

"The IG has turned the police service into a youth wing of a political institution and demonstrating open bias against other political leaders," Ruto said on Thursday during an event at Kunyak Secondary School in Kipkelion West, Kericho County.  



