Kiharu MP Ndindi Nyoro also blamed Interior Cabinet Secretary Fred Matiang'i of lecturing the Judiciary and attempting to muzzle the independence of the institution.  

"We did not know Matiang'i when the President and his deputy were campaigning in 2013 but he now seems to be lecturing the DP who should be his boss," he added.  

Kapseret MP Oscar Sudi termed as disrespectful for Cabinet Secretaries to undermine Dr Ruto as he cautioned that they will soon be held accountable for their actions.  

Ruto being frustrated 

South Mugirango MP Sylvanus Osoro however revealed that the DP is being frustrated by top government officials due to his bid to take over the leadership of the country.  

"We are calling on you to pray for us. We are going through a lot.  

"But I'm happy we have just about 12 months for them to leave office for DP Ruto to take over and lead the country to the right direction.  

Other leaders who castigated the government officials over alleged unfair mistreatment of the DP supporters included Kericho Governor Prof Paul Chepkwony and Soy MP Caleb Kositany. DP allies promised to capture all the seats in Thursday's polls, but realised things were different on the ground. The BBI Bill to be introduced in Parliament as the country’s marches towards a plebiscite gains momentum. Odinga's personal doctor David Olunya says ODM leader is responding well to treatment. Senator Moi will visit Bomet County Friday, while the Deputy President will be in West Pokot County on Saturday.